  "why": "The paper does not demonstrate or evaluate whether fault-inducing inputs discovered on one model transfer to other models, nor does it include explicit design choices to promote cross-model transferability (e.g., using surrogate models or cross-model feedback). DLFuzz is described and evaluated as generating adversarial inputs against a single DNN under test (and is explicitly designed to avoid needing multiple models or cross-referencing oracles). The experiments run DLFuzz separately on several pre-trained models, but there is no reuse of adversarial inputs from one model to test another and no cross-model transfer results are reported.",
